      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Expose verified ClawHub source in skill verify output",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRefs #92077. Follow-up to #93506.\n\nThis PR exposes the trusted ClawHub source provenance that #93506 started consuming in one more user-visible surface:\n\n- Adds `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl` to `openclaw skills verify` JSON output when ClawHub verification returns server-resolved GitHub provenance.\n- Reuses the same trust-boundary helper for install persistence and verify output, so unsupported provenance shapes remain untrusted.\n- Builds the promoted source URL from server-resolved `repo` + `commit` + optional `path`, producing a commit-pinned GitHub URL instead of trusting the raw `provenance.url` field, which can point at a mutable ref such as `main`.\n- Documents the new verify JSON field in the skills CLI docs.\n\nThis does not read or promote self-attested `SKILL.md` metadata from #92860. It also does not replace #93314, which is still the readback half for provenance already written to local `.clawhub/origin.json`.\n\n## Behavior addressed\n\nUsers and tooling consuming `openclaw skills verify` JSON can now find the verified source URL under the OpenClaw-owned metadata envelope without guessing whether raw ClawHub `provenance.url` is immutable or trusted.\n\nUnavailable provenance or any non-`server-resolved-github-import` provenance stays only in the raw verification envelope and is not promoted as `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `openclaw skills verify` JSON now promotes only server-resolved ClawHub GitHub provenance into a commit-pinned `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl`.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on macOS with Node v22.18.0 and pnpm 11.2.2. The local Node version is below the repo-requested `>=22.19.0`, so commands print the existing engine warning, but all targeted checks exited 0.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```sh\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/skills-cli.verify.test.ts src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.test.ts\npnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.ts src/cli/skills-cli.ts src/cli/skills-cli.verify.test.ts src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.test.ts docs/cli/skills.md\nnode scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.ts src/cli/skills-cli.ts src/cli/skills-cli.verify.test.ts src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.test.ts\npnpm tsgo:core\npnpm tsgo:test:src\ngit diff --check\npnpm docs:list\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\nsrc/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.test.ts: 40 passed\nsrc/cli/skills-cli.verify.test.ts: 3 passed\noxfmt: all matched files use the correct format\noxlint: passed on changed source/test files\ntsgo:core: passed\ntsgo:test:src: passed\ngit diff --check: passed\ndocs:list: passed\nautoreview clean: no accepted/actionable findings reported\noverall: patch is correct\n```\n\nObserved result after fix:\n\n- A verification response with `provenance.source: \"server-resolved-github-import\"`, `url: \".../tree/main/agentreceipt\"`, `repo: \"openclaw/skills\"`, `commit: \"def456\"`, and `path: \"agentreceipt\"` produces `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl: \"https://github.com/openclaw/skills/tree/def456/agentreceipt\"`.\n- A verification response with `provenance.source: \"unavailable\"` and a URL does not produce `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl`.\n- Install persistence continues using the same helper, so server-resolved provenance stored in local lock/origin metadata is also commit-pinned.\n\nWhat was not tested: there is still no live positive ClawHub provenance sample available from production ClawHub, so this PR uses focused CLI/lifecycle tests around the current server-resolved provenance contract.\n",
        "branch": "feature/issue-92077-verified-source-verify-output",
